Python layer hints for z-sandbox (RSA-scale factorization orchestration)

Context to load immediately
@README.md

Scope
- Python orchestrates generation, orchestration, validation, analytics. Java hosts kernels.

Standards
- Use mpmath, sympy, numpy, pandas. Set mp.dps explicitly for runs. Seed RNG=42.
- CSV interchange with Java; keep schemas stable. Store outputs in results/, logs/; visuals in plots/.
- Respect invariants: Z=A(B/e²), κ(n)=d(n)·ln(n+1)/e², θ'(n,k)=φ*((n mod φ)/φ)^k (k≈0.3); verify via mpmath (<1e-16).

Runbook
- Install deps: pip install mpmath sympy numpy pandas pytest pytest-cov
- Tests: python -m pytest -q (add --maxfail=1) and key integrations:
  - PYTHONPATH=python python3 tests/test_lorentz_dilation.py
  - PYTHONPATH=python python3 tests/test_gva_128.py
- Demo sanity: python3 python/rsa260_z5d_runner.py --dps 2000 --k 0.30 --use-z5d-prior --adaptive-step --line-search

Conventions
- Keep modules under python/. Fix imports with explicit PYTHONPATH when invoking.
- Use GMP-ECM via subprocess if needed; gate behind a flag; document in docs/.
- Do not check large artifacts; write to results/ and reference paths.

Safety
- Avoid network unless requested. Prefer vectorized operations; mind battery/thermals on M1.
